<h2>About Woodland War</h2>

<div class="card">
  <h3>What is Woodland War?</h3>
  <p>
    Woodland War is a web-based adaptation of asymmetric woodland strategy games. It allows you to 
    play with friends and family over the internet in real-time, with each player controlling a 
    unique faction with their own rules, abilities, and path to victory.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h3>How to Play</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Create a Game:</strong> Click "Create Game" on the home page to start a new lobby</li>
    <li><strong>Share the Code:</strong> Give your friends the 6-character game code</li>
    <li><strong>Choose Factions:</strong> Each player picks their faction from the available options</li>
    <li><strong>Ready Up:</strong> Once everyone has chosen, mark yourself as ready</li>
    <li><strong>Play!</strong> The host starts the game and you're off!</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h3>Features</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Real-time multiplayer with 2-4 players</li>
    <li>Four unique asymmetric factions</li>
    <li>Interactive game board with drag-and-drop pieces</li>
    <li>In-game chat with your opponents</li>
    <li>Turn-by-turn action log</li>
    <li>Guest play - no account required</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h3>Technical Stack</h3>
  <p>
    Woodland War is built with modern web technologies for a smooth gaming experience:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> React with real-time updates via WebSocket</li>
    <li><strong>Backend:</strong> Node.js with Express and Handlebars for server-rendered pages</li>
    <li><strong>Database:</strong> MongoDB for persistent game storage</li>
    <li><strong>Cache:</strong> Redis for fast real-time game state</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h3>Credits &amp; Inspiration</h3>
  <p>
    This game is inspired by asymmetric woodland strategy board games. All assets are original 
    or generic to avoid any copyright issues. The game mechanics are based on common board game 
    concepts reimagined for web play.
  </p>
  <p>
    Special thanks to all players and testers who helped make this possible!
  </p>
</div>
